# Hermon Frappe CRM - Project Context & Development Guidelines

## Project Overview

This is a **custom fork** of the official [Frappe CRM](https://frappe.io/crm) ([GitHub](https://github.com/frappe/crm)) that we maintain for our multi-tenant SaaS business model. We deploy this customized CRM along with [Frappe WhatsApp](https://cloud.frappe.io/marketplace/apps/frappe_whatsapp) ([GitHub](https://github.com/shridarpatil/frappe_whatsapp)) for each client on Frappe Cloud.

### Business Model
- **Multi-tenancy**: Each client gets their own Frappe site on Frappe Cloud
- **Two-app deployment**: CRM + Frappe WhatsApp for every client
- **Generic features**: All customizations must be applicable to all clients for operational simplicity

## Key Customizations & Features

### 1. SMS Integration
- **Added SMS sending/receiving** via Twilio integration
- **New DocType**: `SMS Message` for tracking SMS communications
- **Frontend components**: `SmsBox.vue`, `SmsArea.vue` for SMS management
- **API endpoints**: `send_sms()`, `get_sms_history()`, `handle_incoming_sms()`
- **Real-time updates**: Socket events for SMS notifications

### 2. Bug Fixes & Improvements
- Fixed various upstream bugs from the original Frappe CRM
- Enhanced communication handling and notifications
- All communications now create notifications for users—this includes loading new events for emails (via the Communication doctype), SMS messages, and more.
- Improved data migration and patch management
- Better error handling and user experience
- **Notification routing**: Fixed Email and SMS notifications to properly route to their respective tabs
- **Navigation**: Fixed lead navigation to properly reload data when clicking notifications

### 3. Disabled Features
- **Deals**: Deal view and functionality are currently disabled
- **Focus**: All development efforts focus solely on Lead management
- Deal-related features and UI are present in the codebase but not actively maintained

### 4. Planned Enhancements
- **Kanban Activity Indicators**: Real-time counts for emails, WhatsApp, notes, tasks
- **Kanban Column Counters**: Show total counts in column headers
- Enhanced socket-based real-time updates
- Better visual feedback for new activities

## Development Guidelines

### 1. Generic Feature Development
- **ALL features must be generic** and applicable to all clients
- Avoid client-specific customizations that can't be reused
- Design features to work across different business models and industries
- Consider scalability and multi-tenancy from the start

### 2. Code Standards
- Follow Frappe Framework conventions and patterns
- Use existing Frappe UI components and design tokens
- Maintain compatibility with Frappe Cloud deployment
- Follow the existing code structure and organization

### 3. Integration Patterns
- **Twilio Integration**: Located in `crm/integrations/twilio/`
- **WhatsApp Integration**: Uses external Frappe WhatsApp app
- **Socket Events**: Follow existing patterns in `crm/api/whatsapp.py`
- **API Endpoints**: Use `@frappe.whitelist()` decorator

### 4. Frontend Development
- **Framework**: Vue 3 with Frappe UI components
- **Styling**: Use Frappe surface/ink tokens for theme adaptability
- **Real-time**: Socket.IO for live updates
- **Components**: Located in `frontend/src/components/`

### 5. Backend Development
- **DocTypes**: Located in `crm/fcrm/doctype/`
- **API Functions**: Located in `crm/api/`
- **Hooks**: Defined in `crm/hooks.py`
- **Patches**: Located in `crm/patches/v1_0/`

## File Structure Context

```
crm/
├── api/                    # API endpoints and business logic
├── fcrm/doctype/          # Custom DocTypes (SMS Message, etc.)
├── integrations/          # Twilio, Exotel integrations
├── overrides/             # Frappe core overrides
├── patches/               # Database migration patches
└── hooks.py               # Frappe app hooks

frontend/
├── src/components/        # Vue components
├── src/pages/            # Main application pages
├── src/stores/           # Pinia stores for state management
└── src/socket.js         # Socket.IO client setup
```

## Deployment Context

- **Platform**: Frappe Cloud (managed hosting)
- **Apps**: CRM + Frappe WhatsApp for each client site
- **Multi-tenancy**: Each client gets isolated Frappe site
- **Updates**: Deploy updates across all client sites

## Development Workflow

1. **Feature Planning**: Ensure feature is generic and reusable
2. **Development**: Follow Frappe conventions and existing patterns
3. **Testing**: Test with multiple client scenarios
4. **Deployment**: Deploy to all client sites on Frappe Cloud
5. **Monitoring**: Track usage and performance across all tenants

## Key Considerations

- **Scalability**: Features must work with hundreds of client sites
- **Maintenance**: Generic features reduce operational complexity
- **Compatibility**: Maintain compatibility with upstream Frappe CRM
- **Performance**: Consider impact on multi-tenant deployment
- **Security**: Ensure proper data isolation between clients

